data.title: Destroyer Sterett returns to San Diego Thursday

data.text:
Missing Fourth of July barbecues by one day, the Navy destroyer Sterett is scheduled to return to San Diego on Thursday after a deployment with the aircraft carrier Abraham Lincoln.

The Sterett traveled in the Western Pacific and Arabian Sea regions and took part in five naval exercises with other countries. The ship also spend time doing maritime security missions.

The destroyer will return home to San Diego Naval Base in the afternoon.

It is the fourth U.S. ship named after Lt. Andrew Sterett, who commanded the Enterprise against Barbary pirates in 1802. Like her namesake, Sterett was also involved in anti-piracy operations during its most recent deployment.
